Here is the complete implementation plan for adding the `mistral-instruct-v3` chat template handler. All changes are **purely additive** — no existing code is modified.

---

## 4 Changes Across 2 Files

### `src/llama-chat.h` — 1 new line
Add `LLM_CHAT_TEMPLATE_MISTRAL_INSTRUCT_V3` before `LLM_CHAT_TEMPLATE_UNKNOWN` in the enum (line 60).

---

### `src/llama-chat.cpp` — 3 additions

**1. Map registration** (before the closing `};` of `LLM_CHAT_TEMPLATES`, line ~80):
```cpp
{ "mistral-instruct-v3", LLM_CHAT_TEMPLATE_MISTRAL_INSTRUCT_V3 },
```

**2. Auto-detection heuristic** (inserted at the **top** of the `else {` block at line 121, before the llama2 checks):
```cpp
if (tmpl_contains("'[INST] ' + system_message")) {
    return LLM_CHAT_TEMPLATE_MISTRAL_INSTRUCT_V3;
}
```
The Mistral v0.3 Jinja template contains `'[INST] '` (no leading space *inside* the literal), distinguishing it from v1's `' [INST] '` (with a leading space). The absence of `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` is already guaranteed by the outer condition having returned `MISTRAL_V7` first.

**3. Formatting handler** (new `else if` block just before the final `} else { return -1; }` at line 903):
```cpp
} else if (tmpl == LLM_CHAT_TEMPLATE_MISTRAL_INSTRUCT_V3) {
    // Mistral Instruct v0.3 — system prepended to first user turn
    std::string system_prompt;
    for (auto message : chat) {
        std::string role(message->role);
        std::string content(message->content);
        if (role == "system") {
            system_prompt += content;
        } else if (role == "user") {
            ss << "[INST] ";
            if (!system_prompt.empty()) {
                ss << system_prompt << "\n\n";
                system_prompt = "";
            }
            ss << content << " [/INST]";
        } else {
            ss << content << "</s>";
        }
    }
```
No `add_ass` branch is needed — `[/INST]` already signals the generation boundary (consistent with v1/v3/v7 handlers).

---

## Detection Priority (after change)
1. `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` → `MISTRAL_V7`
2. `' [INST] ' + system_message` or `[AVAILABLE_TOOLS]` → `MISTRAL_V1 / V3 / V3_TEKKEN`
3. **(NEW)** `'[INST] ' + system_message` → `MISTRAL_INSTRUCT_V3`
4. `<<SYS>>` / `bos_token + '[INST]'` / `content.strip()` → llama2 variants
